## SCRATCHPAD — MANDATORY for multi-step questions

For ANY question requiring more than one data lookup:

```bash
mkdir -p /tmp/scratchpad
# Log EVERY value immediately after extraction:
echo "YEAR=1985 | VALUE=123.4 | SOURCE=bulletin_1986_03 | TABLE=FO-1 | ROW=Total capital" >> /tmp/scratchpad/values.txt
```

**Before calculating, ALWAYS review:**
```bash
echo "=== SCRATCHPAD REVIEW ===" && cat /tmp/scratchpad/values.txt
```

**Why this matters:** After multiple tool calls, early values scroll out of attention. The scratchpad ensures you compute with correct numbers, not hallucinated ones. This is the #1 source of errors without it.

