## PITFALLS

| Pitfall | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Reading entire bulletin files | Use `extract_tables` or `search_corpus` |
| Fiscal/calendar year confusion | FY ends Jun 30 (pre-1977) / Sep 30 (post-1977) |
| Wrong units (millions vs billions) | Check table header row |
| Rounding intermediate values | Only round final result |
| Using first plausible answer | Use `find_latest_value` — bulletins revise prior figures |
| ESF "Capital account" ≠ total | ESF capital = sum of ALL capital lines |
| Missing `%` sign | Only include if question uses it |
| Missing unit suffix | Re-read: "Report in millions" → `36080 million` |
| Missing text verdict | `[0.012]` wrong → `[0.012, surplus]` |
| Dropped `$` sign | When question/table uses `$` → `$37,921,314` |
| Comma stripping | Preserve `2,602`; brackets: `[374,443, 381,327]` |
| Multiple tables same bulletin | Read header of EACH match |
| Chart question burnout | Max 5 min; search ±50 lines for underlying table |
| Scratchpad skipped | ALWAYS log values; ALWAYS review before computing |
| NaN or empty values | Try alternate grep patterns, adjacent bulletins |

